    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-03T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-03T06:00:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/143: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-03T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 3, 1937—noon.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 3—8:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83. Your 25, March 2, 7 p.m. I have no comment to offer on the first paragraph.
                    In my opinion the second paragraph raises considerations which might lead to
                    unnecessary complications in the future and not only would be misunderstood here
                    but might well be regarded as an affront. In its place I suggest the following:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Department’s action in this respect is in accordance with its usual
                            practice of terminating consular activities in any district where
                            American interests no longer require such services.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0702" n="691" xml:id="pg_691"/>
                <p>I should welcome the Department’s authorization to communicate this decision
                    orally to the Minister for Foreign Affairs before public announcement is made
                    but if there is not sufficient time the Department might care to communicate it
                    orally to Ambassador Suvich.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
